<p><b>What does 5x114 mean on wheels?</b> A bolt circle of 5x114. 3 mm would indicate a 5 lug pattern on a circle with a diameter of 114.3mm (or 4.5").</p>
<p><b>Who uses 5x114 3 bolt pattern?</b> 75 bolt pattern is still being used but again mostly by GM, Ford and Dodge use mosy 5x114. 3 which is one of the reasons most police cars are Ford or Dodges because the rims are interchangable.</p>
<p><b>Is 114.3 the same as 4.5 bolt pattern?</b> Note: 5×114.3 is the 5×4.5 bolt pattern in mm; 4.5 inches equals 114.3 millimeters. You may find 5×114.3 written in some specifications – but it's just the same bolt pattern in millimeters instead of inches.</p>
